WEBVTT

00:02:27.966 --> 00:02:30.510
I was sentenced to irrelevance --

00:02:30.534 --> 00:02:32.177
the opposite of humanity.

00:02:33.249 --> 00:02:34.810
Interestingly,

00:02:34.834 --> 00:02:39.857
it was during those years in prison
that a series of letters redeemed me,

00:02:39.881 --> 00:02:42.720
helped me move beyond
the darkness and the guilt

00:02:42.744 --> 00:02:45.632
associated with the worst
moment of my young life.

00:02:46.205 --> 00:02:48.055
It gave me a sense that I was useful.

00:02:48.938 --> 00:02:50.922
She was 13 years old.

00:02:51.336 --> 00:02:53.884
She had wrote that she saw me as a hero.

00:02:54.498 --> 00:02:55.886
I remember reading that,

00:02:55.910 --> 00:02:58.637
and I remember crying
when I read those words.

00:02:59.414 --> 00:03:01.858
She was one of over 50 students